SUMMARY:Left Off the Blueprint
DESCRIPTION:Good design is invisible. Bad design is something women navigate every day. \nIn public spaces\, designers have rarely looked closely enough at how women actually move through streets\, neighbourhoods\, and informal gathering spaces. In digital infrastructure\, women’s needs and safety are an afterthought\, if considered at all. In healthcare\, the gap is starker still. A space meant for healing leaves too many women negotiating their right to be there\, be it fair inclusion in clinical trials or access to safe examinations.  \nThis panel examines what it would take to change these systems to include those left off the original blueprints.  \nA Q&A with the audience will follow. \nThis event is part of our programming to celebrate International Women’s Day. Music\, theatre\, and conversation: by women\, for everyone. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/left-off-the-blueprint/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Design,Development,Gender,Society
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-1-16.jpg
END:VEVENT
