SUMMARY:Celebrating Women Composers
DESCRIPTION:Sthree Thaal Tharang is a soulful celebration of creativity in music\, weaving together rhythm and resonance in a powerful all-women presentation. The repertoire draws from the vachanas of Akkamahadevi\, addressed to Chenna Mallikarjuna and marked by spiritual intensity and metaphysical longing; the verses of Andal\, whose poetic imagination and theological vision shaped Tamil bhakti literature; and the bhajans of Mirabai\, whose voice articulated a deeply personal and fearless devotion. \nThe programme includes twentieth-century composers\, such as Ambujam Krishna\, known for her lyrical clarity and devotional depth. In addition\, the ensemble revisits compositions popularised by pioneering women performers of the twentieth century\, acknowledging their role in shaping modern concert practice. The evening culminates in laya-oriented creations by Sukanya Ramgopal\, integrating Ghata Tharang with percussive textures and melodic interplay. \nRather than a thematic tribute alone\, Sthree Thaal Tharang situates women not at the margins\, but at the centre of music’s evolving history — as composers\, interpreters\, and custodians of a living tradition. \nThis event is a part of our programming to celebrate International Women’s Day. Music\, theatre\, and conversation: by women\, for everyone. \nSupported by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/women-composers-in-classical-music/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Gender,Heritage,Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_WCICM.jpg
END:VEVENT
