SUMMARY:Stilling
DESCRIPTION:Stillness is not the absence of motion. It is motion in perfect opposition to itself. \nTwo forces rotating in opposite directions meet at a single point. What they produce is not rest\, but a stillness that contains both beginning and end. Perfect containment. \nTen dancers begin with short studies\, building a vocabulary of contradictions with almost algebraic precision. They are disjointed and interconnected at the same time. The performance does not ask you to watch it unfold. It pulls you inward. \nInto the counter. Into the disquiet. Into Stilling. \nCredits:\nChoreography: Padmini Chettur\nSound: Maarten Visser\nDancers: Aarabi Veeraraghavan\, Anoushka Kurien\, Madhushree Basu\, Masoom Parmar\, Pradeep Gupta\, Priyakshi Agarwal\, Ramya Shanmugam\, Revati Shah\, Sravanthi Vakkalanka\, Tushti Aravind \nThis is part of the 7th Edition of Prakriti Excellence in Contemporary Dance Awards (PECDA). This is the first of three full length showcase performances in 2026 PECDA. \nIn collaboration with: \n     \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/stilling/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_S2-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
